Production Outlook
The company estimates its average worldwide oil-equivalent production in 2020 will grow up to 3 percent compared to 2019,
assuming a Brent crude oil price of $60 per barrel and excluding the impact of anticipated 2020 asset sales. This estimate is subject
to many factors and uncertainties, as described beginning on page 30. Refer to the “Review of Ongoing Exploration and Production
Activities in Key Areas,” beginning on page 8, for a discussion of the company’s major crude oil and natural gas development
projects.
