underway, including $4 billion associated with the Future Growth and Wellhead Pressure Management Project at the Tengiz field in
Kazakhstan. Global exploration funding is expected to be about $1 billion. Remaining upstream spend is budgeted for early stage
projects supporting potential future developments. The company monitors crude oil market conditions and is able to adjust future
capital outlays should oil price conditions deteriorate.
Worldwide downstream spending in 2020 is estimated to be $2.8 billion, with $1.6 billion estimated for projects in the United
